title: Police Seeking Suspect Who Stole Salvador Dali Artwork From Gallery
description:
SAN FRANCISCO (BCN)   Police are looking for the suspect who walked into an art gallery  near San Francisco's Union Square on Sunday and stole a piece of art by the  famed Spanish artist Salvador Dali.   According to police, the suspect entered the gallery, located in  the 300 block of Geary Street, sometime between 4:40 and 5:45 p.m.   The suspect then took the artwork, described by police as an  etching, before taking off.   The Police Department's burglary detail is working to find the  suspect and retrieve the valuable etching.   Police are asking anyone with information about the theft to  contact the San Francisco police 24-hour tip line at (415) 575-4444 or to  text-a-tip to TIP411 with the words "SFPD" at the beginning of the message.  Tipsters can remain anonymous.
